712519f-b.title: Manhattan: 38th Street (West) - 10th Avenue
712519f-b.text:
Vest 38th Street (imrediate foreground) north side, east of
Tenth Avenue, showing an extensive demolition in a progressive
arrangement north-eastward, in a series of 3 views. No. 1 discloses
what the writer believes to be the rears of No's. 452 and 45O 4.
39th Street; No. 2, the rear of No. 436 W. 39th Street; and No. 3,
the rear of No. 426-24 W. 39th Street. Across the latter appears
the huge EcGraw-Hill Bldg. on 4. 42nd Street. This demolition was
necessitated by te Lincoln Tunnel construction which will have its
entrance here.
March 18, 1938.
Views 1, 2 and 3.
P. L. Sperr,
